"<div>\n  <h1>Cheddar and Scallop Noodle Bowl with Kale and Cranberry Sauce</h1>\n  <h3>Ingredients:</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>8 oz. dried noodles</li>\n    <li>1 lb. fresh scallops, cleaned and trimmed</li>\n    <li>1 bunch kale, leaves torn into bite-sized pieces</li>\n    <li>1 cup cheddar cheese, shredded</li>\n    <li>1 cup cranberry sauce, sweetened</li>\n    <li>2 tbsp. olive oil</li>\n    <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h3>Directions:</h3>\n  <ol>\n    <li>Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add noodles and cook according to package instructions.</li>\n    <li>In a separate skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add scallops and cook for 2-3 minutes per side until browned and cooked through. Remove from skillet and set aside.</li>\n    <li>In the same skillet, add torn kale leaves and sauté for 2-3 minutes until wilted. Remove from skillet and set aside.</li>\n    <li>Drain cooked noodles and divide them into four bowls. Top with cooked scallops and sautéed kale.</li>\n    <li>Sprinkle shredded cheddar cheese over the top of each bowl.</li>\n    <li>Serve with a generous spoonful of sweetened cranberry sauce on top of each bowl.</li>\n    <li>Add salt and pepper to taste, if desired.</li>\n  </ol>\n</div>"